ll,"body":"When importing a jsonl file with \"label\" annotations, if any texts have any length 0 annotations, Docanno will fail to import the labels. \r\n\r\nThe texts and metadata are successfully imported, but no labels will be available.\r\n\r\nLabels are available after import:\r\n```json\r\n{\"data\": \"EU rejects German call to boycott British lamb.\", \"label\": [ [0, 2, \"ORG\"]]}\r\n{\"data\": \"Peter Blackburn\", \"label\": [ [0, 15, \"PERSON\"] ]}\r\n{\"data\": \"President Obama\", \"label\": [ [10, 15, \"PERSON\"] ]}\r\n```\r\n\r\nLabels are not imported:\r\n```json\r\n{\"data\": \"EU rejects German call to boycott British lamb.\", \"label\": [ [0, 2, \"ORG\"]]}\r\n{\"data\": \"Peter Blackburn\", \"label\": [ [15, 15, \"PERSON\"] ]}\r\n{\"data\": \"President Obama\", \"label\": [ [10, 15, \"PERSON\"] ]}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think an Exception should be raised in this situation, or these labels should be skipped with a Warning message.","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/issues/1898/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/issues/1898/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}